{
  "texts": [
    "Dataset and justification CKHK-22 characterizes the robustness with an exceptional 24-class balance and encompasses multiple classes representing various clinical conditions.",
    "This dataset integrates different sources from existing datasets, such as CVC Clinic DB, Kvasir2, and Hyper Kvasir, hence guaranteeing well-class-balanced distribution in studies involving polyp detection.",
    "Also, to account for questions about generalizability, a series of on-spot ongoing processes for this proposed framework involves their viability over more datasets from various geospatially located places and image acquiring systems.",
    "This might turn the tide in proving to make a robustness assurance from their proposed model when a real-time clinical trial becomes practical.",
    "The CKHK-22 dataset analysis is the initial stage in the segmentation of colorectal cancer."
  ]
}